<TITLE> China coal mine blast traps 50 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Beijing, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - At least 50 people were trapped after a gas blast ripped through a coal mine in north China on Thursday, Xinhua news agency reported. The explosion happened at a mine in Hongtong county in the northern province of Shanxi, China's largest coal-producing province. The country has been trying to tighten safety regulations but its coal industry is still the world's deadliest, claiming close to 5,000 lives last year
